%N A393540 Least composite divisible by the sum of two of its distinct prime divisors in exactly n different ways.
%C A393540 All the numbers found are divisible by 30.
%C A393540 Terms of the sequence which can be divided by all the possible sums of 2 of their different prime divisors are 2520, 65520, 720720, 27387360, 465585120, 53542288800, ...
%C A393540 binomial(omega(a(n)), 2) >= n. - _David A. Corneth_, Mar 06 2026
%H A393540 Paolo P. Lava, <a href="/A393540/b393540.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..50</a>
%e A393540 a(4) = 420 because its prime factors are 2, 3, 5, 7 and
%e A393540   420/(2+3) = 84; 420/(2+5) = 60; 420/(3+7) = 42; 420/(5+7) = 35.
%e A393540 a(10) = 65520 because its prime factors are 2, 3, 5, 7, 13 and
%e A393540   65520/(2+3) = 13104;  65520/(2+5) = 9360;  65520/(2+7) = 7280;  65520/(2+13) = 4368;
%e A393540   65520/(3+5) = 8190;  65520/(3+7) = 6552;  65520/(3+13) = 4095;  65520/(5+7) = 5460;
%e A393540   65520/(5+13) = 3640;  65520/(7+13) = 3276.
